pesticide.PPE: Wear long-sleeved shirt and long pants; socks and shoes; chemical-resistant gloves such as Barrier Laminate, Butyl Rubber ≥ 14 mils, Nitrile Rubber ≥ 14 mils, and Viton ≥ 14 mils. Follow manufacturer’s instructions for cleaning and maintaining PPE.

Active_Ingredients.name: Azoxystrobin
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: inhibits the Qo site within the electron transport system and disrupts membrane synthesis by blocking demethylation

Safety_Information.general_Info: For medical emergencies, call the poison control center at 1-800-222-1222. For information about this product, call Yifan Bio-Tech Group Co., LTD at +86 15868088686 or email yifan@chinayifan.com (China), or contact the National Pesticides Information Center (NPIC) at 1-800-858-7378, Monday through Friday 8 AM to 12 PM PST or at http:/npic.orst.edu/
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. DO NOT induce vomiting unless told to do so by the poison control center or doctor. DO NOT give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably mouth-to-mouth, if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor or going for treatment.
